column2: The user interface felt intuitive to use
column3: (For relevant users) I experienced few to no complications when installing and setting up the system
column4: The provided robots facilitate for creating a diverse set of missions
column5: I experienced few to no errors with scaling when adding a large number of robots
column6: Based on my experience, I found the system to be useful to plan simple missions
column7: I experienced few to no errors when executing the provided missions
column8: I experienced few to no errors when creating new missions
column9: I experienced few to no errors when modifying a mission
column10: I found the syntax of the DSL to be simple to understand
column11: I experienced few to no errors while using the web editor for the DSL
column12: I experienced few to no complications with the communication between the robots
column13: I found it useful to have different task allocation algorithms to choose from
column14: I found it useful to be able to insert my own task allocation algorithm
column15: Overall, the system facilitates well for extensibility
column16: I would recommend this system to other users
column17: I would recommend this system to other developers
column18: Based on my experience with the system, I believe it is a good starting environment for robotics developers to add their own robots and implementations
